8#include <stddef.h>

10#define CHECK_LT(a, b) if ((a) >= b) return 0
11
12static const char multibyte_length_table[16] = {
13 0, 0, 0, 0, /* 0x00-0x3F */
14 0, 0, 0, 0, /* 0x40-0x7F */
15 0, 0, 0, 0, /* 0x80-0xBF */
16 2, 2, 3, 4, /* 0xC0-0xFF */
17};
18
19
20/*
21 * Get length of multibyte character sequence starting at a given byte.
22 * Returns zero if the byte is not a valid leading byte in UTF-8.
23 */
24static int GetMultibyteLength(char c) {
25 return multibyte_length_table[((unsigned char)c) >> 4];
26}
27
28/*
29 * Moves pointers one byte forward.
30 */
31static void NextPos(const unsigned char** pos,
32 const char** key,
33 const char** multibyte_start)
34{
35 ++*pos;
36 if (*multibyte_start) {
37 /* Advance key to next byte in multibyte sequence. */
38 ++*key;
39 /* Reset multibyte_start if last byte in multibyte sequence was consumed. */
40 if (*key - *multibyte_start == GetMultibyteLength(c: **multibyte_start))
41 *multibyte_start = 0;
42 } else {
43 if (GetMultibyteLength(c: **key)) {
44 /* Multibyte prefix was matched in the dafsa, start matching multibyte
45 * content in next round. */
46 *multibyte_start = *key;
47 } else {
48 /* Advance key as a single byte character was matched. */
49 ++*key;
50 }
51 }
52}
53
54/*
55 * Read next offset from pos.
56 * Returns true if an offset could be read, false otherwise.
57 */
58
59static int GetNextOffset(const unsigned char** pos,
60 const unsigned char* end,
61 const unsigned char** offset)
62{
63 size_t bytes_consumed;
64
65 if (*pos == end)
66 return 0;
67
68 /* When reading an offset the byte array must always contain at least
69 * three more bytes to consume. First the offset to read, then a node
70 * to skip over and finally a destination node. No object can be smaller
71 * than one byte. */
72 CHECK_LT(*pos + 2, end);
73 switch (**pos & 0x60) {
74 case 0x60: /* Read three byte offset */
75 *offset += (((*pos)[0] & 0x1F) << 16) | ((*pos)[1] << 8) | (*pos)[2];
76 bytes_consumed = 3;
77 break;
78 case 0x40: /* Read two byte offset */
79 *offset += (((*pos)[0] & 0x1F) << 8) | (*pos)[1];
80 bytes_consumed = 2;
81 break;
82 default:
83 *offset += (*pos)[0] & 0x3F;
84 bytes_consumed = 1;
85 }
86 if ((**pos & 0x80) != 0) {
87 *pos = end;
88 } else {
89 *pos += bytes_consumed;
90 }
91 return 1;
92}
93
94/*
95 * Check if byte at offset is last in label.
96 */
97
98static int IsEOL(const unsigned char* offset, const unsigned char* end)
99{
100 CHECK_LT(offset, end);
101 return(*offset & 0x80) != 0;
102}
103
104/*
105 * Check if byte at offset matches first character in key.
106 * This version assumes a range check was already performed by the caller.
107 */
108
109static int IsMatchUnchecked(const unsigned char matcher,
110 const char* key,
111 const char* multibyte_start)
112{
113 if (multibyte_start) {
114 /* Multibyte matching mode. */
115 if (multibyte_start == key) {
116 /* Match leading byte, which will also match the sequence length. */
117 return (matcher ^ 0x80) == (const unsigned char)*key;
118 } else {
119 /* Match following bytes. */
120 return (matcher ^ 0xC0) == (const unsigned char)*key;
121 }
122 }
123 /* If key points at a leading byte in a multibyte sequence, but we are not yet
124 * in multibyte mode, then the dafsa should contain a special byte to indicate
125 * a mode switch. */
126 if (GetMultibyteLength(c: *key)) {
127 return matcher == 0x1F;
128 }
129 /* Normal matching of a single byte character. */
130 return matcher == (const unsigned char)*key;
131}
132
133/*
134 * Check if byte at offset matches first character in key.
135 * This version matches characters not last in label.
136 */
137
138static int IsMatch(const unsigned char* offset,
139 const unsigned char* end,
140 const char* key,
141 const char* multibyte_start)
142{
143 CHECK_LT(offset, end);
144 return IsMatchUnchecked(matcher: *offset, key, multibyte_start);
145}
146
147/*
148 * Check if byte at offset matches first character in key.
149 * This version matches characters last in label.
150 */
151
152static int IsEndCharMatch(const unsigned char* offset,
153 const unsigned char* end,
154 const char* key,
155 const char* multibyte_start)
156{
157 CHECK_LT(offset, end);
158 return IsMatchUnchecked(matcher: *offset ^ 0x80, key, multibyte_start);
159}
160
161/*
162 * Read return value at offset.
163 * Returns true if a return value could be read, false otherwise.
164 */
165
166static int GetReturnValue(const unsigned char* offset,
167 const unsigned char* end,
168 const char* multibyte_start,
169 int* return_value)
170{
171 CHECK_LT(offset, end);
172 if (!multibyte_start && (*offset & 0xE0) == 0x80) {
173 *return_value = *offset & 0x0F;
174 return 1;
175 }
176 return 0;
177}

179/*
180 * Looks up the string |key| with length |key_length| in a fixed set of
181 * strings. The set of strings must be known at compile time. It is converted to
182 * a graph structure named a DAFSA (Deterministic Acyclic Finite State
183 * Automaton) by the script psl-make-dafsa during compilation. This permits
184 * efficient (in time and space) lookup. The graph generated by psl-make-dafsa
185 * takes the form of a constant byte array which should be supplied via the
186 * |graph| and |length| parameters. The return value is kDafsaNotFound,
187 * kDafsaFound, or a bitmap consisting of one or more of kDafsaExceptionRule,
188 * kDafsaWildcardRule and kDafsaPrivateRule ORed together.
189 *
190 * Lookup a domain key in a byte array generated by psl-make-dafsa.
191 */
192
193/* prototype to skip warning with -Wmissing-prototypes */
194int LookupStringInFixedSet(const unsigned char*, size_t,const char*, size_t);
195
196int LookupStringInFixedSet(const unsigned char* graph,
197 size_t length,
198 const char* key,
199 size_t key_length)
200{
201 const unsigned char* pos = graph;
202 const unsigned char* end = graph + length;
203 const unsigned char* offset = pos;
204 const char* key_end = key + key_length;
205 const char* multibyte_start = 0;
206
207 while (GetNextOffset(pos: &pos, end, offset: &offset)) {
208 /*char <char>+ end_char offsets
209 * char <char>+ return value
210 * char end_char offsets
211 * char return value
212 * end_char offsets
213 * return_value
214 */
215 int did_consume = 0;
216
217 if (key != key_end && !IsEOL(offset, end)) {
218 /* Leading <char> is not a match. Don't dive into this child */
219 if (!IsMatch(offset, end, key, multibyte_start))
220 continue;
221 did_consume = 1;
222 NextPos(pos: &offset, key: &key, multibyte_start: &multibyte_start);
223 /* Possible matches at this point:
224 * <char>+ end_char offsets
225 * <char>+ return value
226 * end_char offsets
227 * return value
228 */
229
230 /* Remove all remaining <char> nodes possible */
231 while (!IsEOL(offset, end) && key != key_end) {
232 if (!IsMatch(offset, end, key, multibyte_start))
233 return -1;
234 NextPos(pos: &offset, key: &key, multibyte_start: &multibyte_start);
235 }
236 }
237 /* Possible matches at this point:
238 * end_char offsets
239 * return_value
240 * If one or more <char> elements were consumed, a failure
241 * to match is terminal. Otherwise, try the next node.
242 */
243 if (key == key_end) {
244 int return_value;
245
246 if (GetReturnValue(offset, end, multibyte_start, return_value: &return_value))
247 return return_value;
248 /* The DAFSA guarantees that if the first char is a match, all
249 * remaining char elements MUST match if the key is truly present.
250 */
251 if (did_consume)
252 return -1;
253 continue;
254 }
255 if (!IsEndCharMatch(offset, end, key, multibyte_start)) {
256 if (did_consume)
257 return -1; /* Unexpected */
258 continue;
259 }
260 NextPos(pos: &offset, key: &key, multibyte_start: &multibyte_start);
261 pos = offset; /* Dive into child */
262 }
263
264 return -1; /* No match */
265}

267/* prototype to skip warning with -Wmissing-prototypes */
268int GetUtfMode(const unsigned char *graph, size_t length);
269
270int GetUtfMode(const unsigned char *graph, size_t length)
271{
272 return length > 0 && graph[length - 1] < 0x80;
273}
